Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Science Librarian Vancouver , BC Description Job Description:The Langara Library is seeking a librarian for an 8-month, .75 FTE position backfilling librarians who have been seconded to other work at Langara. Our new team member will serve as the Subject Librarian for several programs: Applied Science, Biology, Chemistry, Mathematics / Statistics, Physics, and Science.Working with the reference and instruction teams, this position will provide reference and research support services, teach library classes, and serve as a liaison to several instructional departments.snəw̓eyəɬ leləm̓ - Langara College is a teaching-focused community college committed to providing accessible, affordable, high-quality education. The ideal candidate brings a student-centered approach to academic librarianship and a strong science background.Start Date: September 1, 2023End Date: April 30, 2024Duties &amp; Responsibilities:Our new team member will:Provide cross-disciplinary reference services, online and in personPlan and deliver information literacy instruction for their subject areasAssist with collections management activities for their subject areas as neededDevelop relationships and liaise with instructional and College departments, primarily in the sciencesCreate and/or modify subject and course guides using the LibGuides platformQualifications Required:Education Master’s degree from an ALA-accredited program in library or information scienceTwo years related work experience as a professional librarian (academic libraries preferred), or an equivalent combination of prior work experiencesSkills &amp; AbilitiesStrong interpersonal and intercultural skillsDemonstrated ability to work independently and as part of a teamExcellent written and oral communication skillsAbility to translate complex concepts into easily understood termsDemonstrated ability to develop and deliver effective and engaging library instruction, both in an online environment and in personStrong project management and organizational skillsDemonstrated initiative, creativity, and problem-solving skillsAcademic credentials or work experience in the sciences an assetThis position is .75 and expected to work roughly a 22.5-hour week. Salary is based on the Langara Faculty Association pay scale and has a range of $$4,360-$6,990 monthly. Posted salary is pro-rated based on hours of work. Placement on the scale is a set calculation based on previous experience. More information can be found in the LFA Collective Agreement.Submit your application online: Employment Opportunities (myworkdayjobs.com) Compensation $4,360 - $6,990 Monthly. Placement on the scale is a set calculation based on previous experience Closes: 9 July, 2023 Langara College Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
