Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Hansard Indexer Regina , SK Description The Legislative Assembly Service of Saskatchewan (LAS) provides the administration and support required for the operation of the Legislative Assembly and provides organizational continuity from one Legislature to the next. The Parliamentary Publications branch exists to produce the Debates and Proceedings, publish indexes, and support various digital publishing initiatives of the official records of the Legislative Assembly of Saskatchewan. The Indexer develops and delivers subject-based, cross-referenced index publications for the official reports of the Legislative Assembly of Saskatchewan and its committees. This position analyzes the subject of debates to create an accurate and thorough tool for the retrieval of information. The Indexer analyzes trends and issues in indexing, identifies and develops options and solutions, and makes policy or procedural recommendations.For more information, please see the full job posting at: Hansard Indexer (legassembly.sk.ca)Interested candidates should submit a letter of interest and resume by 5:00 p.m. (CST) Friday, July 14, 2023 to careers@legassembly.sk.ca Please quote competition 1038157 in the subject of your email. Compensation $4,996 to $6,497 per month Closes: 14 July, 2023 Saskatchewan Legislative Assembly Regina , SK Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
