Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Services &amp; Support Associate – Library Systems &amp; Metadata Full-Time Maternity Leave Contract Toronto , ON Description Services &amp; Support Associate – Library Systems &amp; MetadataFull-Time Maternity Leave ContractOntario Colleges Library Service (OCLS)Job TypeFull-time (37.5 hrs. per week) 18-month maternity leave contractOur OrganizationOntario Colleges Library Service (OCLS) is a not-for-profit organization funded by the Ministry of Colleges and Universities to support Ontario’s publicly assisted colleges and their libraries. We have a strong reputation for service excellence and the college libraries trust us to deliver services and expertise in line with our mandate to create efficiencies, cost savings, and capacity across the system. Our reputation would not have been built, nor could it be maintained, without the skills, knowledge, and experience of the extraordinary members of the OCLS team.Your OpportunityWe are seeking an enthusiastic, customer-focused Services &amp; Support Associate to join our Services team. Reporting to the Manager of Services, you will work closely with the Library Systems &amp; Metadata Coordinator and other members of the Services team to deliver exemplary customer support to Ontario’s 24 college libraries. You will have the opportunity to use your library training and strong service orientation to support college library clients across OCLS’s services and systems, including shared library management systems, catalogues, and e-resource access and authentication tools.This is an excellent career opportunity for a self-directed library professional with a solid foundation and interest in library systems, metadata management, and customer service. As a key member of the OCLS team, you’ll work with remarkable colleagues who support each other to meet the system and service requirements of our college clients.Your ResponsibilitiesServe as a key contact for college library staff and vendors to support the smooth and efficient delivery of services to the college librariesWorking as a member of the Help Desk frontline support team, participate in the triage and resolution of incoming support ticketsDistribute and maintain shared metadata for eresource collections across the college systemSet up and troubleshoot remote access issues using EZproxyAssist with an internal information management project in Confluence and SharePointIn collaboration with your colleagues, create and maintain internal and external-facing documentation and communications in support of servicesWork with other OCLS staff to develop tools, protocols, and services that improve efficiency and workflowsMaintain knowledge of relevant trends and issues for college library services and resourcesParticipate in additional services and projects as assignedHere’s What You’ll NeedThe qualifications listed below are highly desirable but not necessarily mandatory. You are invited to demonstrate how your education skills, knowledge, and experience would best fit this position in your letter of application.Work experience and training:Post-secondary diploma in a Library &amp; Information Technician program or related discipline (required); a Bachelor’s degree would be an asset1-2 years’ experience working in or with libraries; experience in an academic library or library consortium setting is considered an assetDemonstrated experience providing outstanding customer serviceSkills and knowledge:Experience working with Alma/Primo VEExperience working with MARC records in MARCedit, setting up macros and cataloguing a wide range of materials and media using RDA standardsExperience with collaboration tools, e.g. Confluence, Office 365 (incl. SharePoint, OneDrive, Teams) and/or Google Workspace applicationsAttributesDemonstrated ownership and pride in the quality of customer service provided to both internal and external customersExcellent problem solving and analytical abilitiesOutstanding oral and written communication skills, with the ability to synthesize complex or ambiguous information clearly and conciselyExcellent organizational skills, with the ability to manage competing prioritiesAbility to work both independently and as part of a teamDetail-oriented with strong administrative skillsThe following would be considered assets:Experience with information managementExperience with technical writingFamiliarity with metadata schemas such as Dublin CoreFluency in FrenchWhat OCLS Offers Competitive compensation commensurate with experience; the starting salary for this position is $26/hr, plus 2% in lieu of benefits, and a contract completion bonus Two weeks annual vacation Personal leave days Flexible work arrangements in a hybrid model CAAT Pension Plan (optional) Employee and family assistance programBe part of a close-knit, collaborative team of smart, hardworking professionals and join OCLS in providing quality services to Ontario’s publicly funded colleges and their libraries. Visit our website (http://www.ocls.ca) for more details and view the OCLS Strategic Plan for our values, mission, and additional information.Additional InformationOCLS welcomes applications from those who would contribute to the further diversification of our staff, including, but not limited to, Indigenous Peoples, persons with disabilities, and persons of any sexual or gender identity, ethnicity, or age.OCLS is an equal opportunity employer and strives to ensure that its hiring process meets the needs of all persons with disabilities. As such, OCLS will provide reasonable accommodation for any applicant, as requested during the hiring process.Application DeadlineApplications must be received by July 4, 2023. Applications are reviewed as they are received.Position Start DateThe targeted start date for this position is July/August 2023.How to ApplyInterested and qualified candidates may apply by submitting a letter of application, current resume, and a list of three references in a single file labelled with “Your Name_#162” via e-mail to applications@ocls.ca quoting “Your Name - #162” in the subject line. Only those candidates selected for interviews will be contacted.A web version of this posting can be found at: https://www.ocls.ca/careers Compensation Competitive compensation commensurate with experience; the starting salary for this position is $26/hr, plus 2% in lieu of benefits, and a contract completion bonus Closes: 4 July, 2023 Ontario Colleges Library Service Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
