Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Cataloguing and Metadata Librarian Halifax , NS Description Department: Patrick Power Library Type of Employment: Permanent Full-time Group Affiliation: SMUFUThe Patrick Power Library seeks an energetic and innovative professional librarian to lead our cataloguing programs into the future. We require an individual who is excited about working with others to explore and develop new ways to approach the description, organization and access to information resources. The successful applicant will report to the University Librarian within a collegial working environment.Job Information and ResponsibilitiesGeneral Responsibilities:Manages Library catalogue and discovery layer databases, and configures these and related online systems, via the Novanet consortium Integrated Library System.Manages metadata for Saint Mary's library collections.Supervises Cataloguing and Metadata staff.Serves as Library Liaison for assigned academic departments. Liaises with faculty to select materials and assess collections for course proposals and program reviews.Delivers information literacy sessions and research services as required.Participates in library management and consortium committees and activities.Specific Responsibilities:Manages and configures metadata for access to Saint Mary's print and electronic resources in the Novanet library catalogue, the Novanet discovery service (currently ExLibris Primo VE), and the Novanet link resolver system (currently Alma).Manages and ensures the integrity and quality of metadata for Saint Mary’s materials in Novanet.Collaboratively manages the generation of analytic statistics on Saint Mary’s Library collections and their usage.Manages access to open digital collections via the Novanet discovery service and the Novanet library system.Manages Saint Mary’s Library Catalogue interface configuration within the Novanet shared catalogue consortium.Provides expertise and training for library staff and departments on metadata and standards related issues.Manages and configures the license and copyright permission information system.Manages and configures metadata in the library institutional repository (currently DSpace) in cooperation with the University Archivist; collaborates to collect faculty publications and other materials in the repository.Participates in local, regional, national, or international committees and organizations regarding issues or discussions related to areas of responsibility.Experience and Education RequirementsA Master's degree in library or information studies from an ALA-accredited program.Minimum of two years’ professional librarian experience working in an academic library.Thorough understanding of cataloguing, metadata, database management and digital content technologies.Significant experience with managing, loading and quality control of metadata records including large record sets.Outstanding technical skills and a demonstrated ability to analyze and solve systems difficulties.Awareness of current issues and trends in metadata management, open access, digital content, and scholarly publications.Experience with Integrated Library Systems and Discovery services.Experience supervising staff.Ability to work effectively with patrons and colleagues in a team environment.Self-motivated, ability to work independently.Excellent oral and written communication skills.Asset Qualifications Experience with Ex Libris Alma and Primo VE.Managing staff in a unionized environment.Teaching and presenting experience.Application Details Apply for this opportunity online using our online application system through Career Beacon. Click on "Apply Now" and complete all required information fields. Qualified candidates should submit the following with their application: Note: These should be merged into one document. ResumeCover LetterThree Professional References Applications must be received by 4:30 PM on the closing date of July 14, 2023. Late applications may not receive consideration. We appreciate all applications and note that only candidates selected for an interview will be contacted. No telephone calls please. At Saint Mary’s University, equity and diversity are integral to excellence and enrich our community. As an institution committed to fostering an environment of inclusion and respect, we encourage all qualified candidates to apply; however, preference will be given to applicants who self-identify as Black/African Nova Scotians, Indigenous peoples, racialized persons/visible minorities, persons with disabilities and women. If you require accommodations during the recruitment process, please contact Suzanne.vandenHoogen@smu.ca.About Saint Mary’s UniversitySaint Mary’s University is one of Canada’s top primary undergraduate universities--known for its international collaborations, leadership in entrepreneurship, and research that benefits local and global communities. Our programs in Arts, Science, Graduate Studies and the Sobey School of Business are among Canada’s best and feature professors who are committed to the success of their students. Saint Mary’s provides our 7,000 students with a place that fosters possibility, excellent research opportunities, and distinguished graduate and professional programs combined with a caring community. Nestled in the heart of Halifax, Nova Scotia, on Canada’s east coast, Saint Mary’s University is marked by iconic buildings, green spaces and fresh ocean air. The Saint Mary’s University community is committed to a prosperous future for the world—a world without limits.Learn more about working at Saint Mary’s University here and follow us on LinkedIn, Facebook, Twitter and Instagram! Compensation An appointment at the rank of Librarian I or II is anticipated. Salary is based on experience and qualifications. Salary ranges as of September 1, 2022, are $62,114 to $67,168 (Librarian I) and $68,687 to $78,068 (Librarian II) respectively. Closes: 14 July, 2023 Saint Mary's University Halifax , NS Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
